                        "displayName": "Jonathan Keane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "body": "This is super helpful, thanks.  When you say \"a rough approximation of our current rules\" do you mean these are what should already be implemented in coercing join keys, or is that a proposal of what we should add?\r\n\r\nThose rules all look reasonable to me, one that I'm slightly confused by (and might just be a typo?) is:\r\n\r\n\"int + int / uint + uint => widest type (e.g. int32 + int16 => int16)\" \r\nshould that be:\r\n\"int + int / uint + uint => widest type (e.g. int32 + int16 => int32)\"",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/rest/api/2/user?username=jonkeane",
                        "name": "jonkeane",
                        "key": "jonkeane",
                        "avatarUrls": {
                            "48x48": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?avatarId=34057",
                            "24x24": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=small&avatarId=34057",
                            "16x16": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=xsmall&avatarId=34057",
                            "32x32": "https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/useravatar?size=medium&avatarId=34057"
                        },
                        "displayName": "Jonathan Keane",
                        "active": true,
                        "timeZone": "Etc/UTC"
                    },
                    "created": "2022-04-13T19:09:18.709+0000",
